<h3>About-</h3>
<ul>
<li>BRIC- Coined by <strong>Jim O' Neil</strong> (Chair of Goldman Sachs)</li>
<li>1st BRIC Summit - Russia 2009</li>
<li><strong>ECONOMIC AND POLITICAL REGIONAL ORG</strong></li>
<li>Official Languages- Portuguese, Russian, Hindi, Mandarin, English</li>
<li>Approx 40% of World Population</li>
<li>30% of World Area</li>
<li>22% of Gross World GDP</li></ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Challenges</h3>
<ul>
<li>Doubtful cooperation due to China's unprecedented Growth (Compared to other 4)</li>
<li>RCEP- More fruitful</li>
<li>High geographical distance- difficult to work upon a "common trade agenda"</li>
<li>2019- S&amp;P Global Ratings raised question over "relevance" of BRICS</li>
<li>% wise contribution to GDP of group (68% by China alone)</li></ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Opportunities</h3>
<ul>
<li>Can gain politically by coming together (together 13.24% voting share in World Bank)</li>
<li>NDB-Shanghai- lend for infra projects to any developing country- all countries have equal share
<ul>
<li><span style="color:#8e44ad">NDB opened office in GIFT india</span></li></ul></li>
<li>BRICS CRA (Contingent Reserve Arrangement)</li>
<li>RIC can offer alternative to western institutions forming another pole in multipolar world.
<ul>
<li>India aims to build SFMS (sovereign financial messaging system) like SWIFT - internationalsation of rupee</li>
<li>Rupee rouble exchange&nbsp;</li>
<li>&nbsp;</li></ul></li></ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>12th BRICS Summit</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Theme- "Global Stability, Shared Security and Innovative Growth"</strong></li>
<li>Host- Russia</li>
<li>Terrorism, Trade, Health, Energy, Ways to offset Pandemic</li>
<li>India focused on-
<ul>
<li>Multilateralism
<ul>
<li>Reforms in WTO, IMF, WHO, UN</li>
<li>Increase their effectiveness</li>
<li>Change needed with time</li></ul></li>
<li>On Terrorism
<ul>
<li><strong>"There is always a black sheep in the family"- Putin</strong></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul>
